 as the damp macadam at night. Woe! Woe! Question thy crime. Twill show the depth of thy guilt. Dark are the clouds, denser they grow. The Hunter comes riding his terrible steed. Ho-yo-to-ho! Ho-yo-to-ho!'

(Shall I tell him to stop? thought Krug. What's the use? Hell is full of these mummers.)

